# Plan: Stepper Compound Component for shadcn/ui

## Context

shadcn/ui has no built-in stepper/wizard component. Multi-step onboarding and form wizards are a common UI pattern. This adds a `Stepper` compound component that follows all existing conventions in the registry — pure semantic HTML (no Radix primitives needed), React context for state sharing, `data-slot` attributes, Tailwind with `cn()`, and both horizontal and vertical orientations.

**Constraint**: Do NOT modify any existing files. Only create new files and append registry entries.

---

## Files to Create (3 new files)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` | Component implementation |
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` | Horizontal demo |
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-vertical-demo.tsx` | Vertical demo with content panels |

## Files to Modify (2 registry files — append only)

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` | Append 1 entry before closing `]` |
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` | Append 2 entries before closing `]` |

---

## Step 1 — Create `stepper.tsx`

**Path**: `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx`

### Architecture

Two React contexts:
- **`StepperContext`** (root-level): `{ orientation, activeStep, onStepChange }`
- **`StepperItemContext`** (per-step): `{ step, state, disabled }` where `state` is `"active" | "completed" | "inactive"`

Custom hooks `useStepper()` and `useStepperItem()` throw if called outside their provider.

Controlled + uncontrolled state: `activeStep` prop (controlled) and `defaultStep` prop (uncontrolled) following the same pattern as `SidebarProvider`.

### Sub-components (7 total)

#### `Stepper` — Root container
```tsx
"use client"
// Props: orientation ("horizontal"|"vertical", default "horizontal"),
//        activeStep?, defaultStep?, onStepChange?, className, ...divProps
// Renders: <div data-slot="stepper" data-orientation={orientation} className="group/stepper flex ...">
//          wrapped in StepperContext.Provider
// Classes:
//   data-[orientation=horizontal]:flex-row data-[orientation=horizontal]:items-start
//   data-[orientation=vertical]:flex-col data-[orientation=vertical]:items-start
```

#### `StepperItem` — Per-step wrapper
```tsx
// Props: step (number, 1-indexed), disabled? (boolean), className, ...divProps
// Computes state from context: step===activeStep→"active", step<activeStep→"completed", else→"inactive"
// Renders: <div data-slot="stepper-item" data-state={state} data-disabled={disabled?"":undefined}>
//          wrapped in StepperItemContext.Provider
// Classes (use group-data-[orientation=...]/stepper: selectors from root):
//   group/stepper-item flex shrink-0
//   group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper:flex-col
//   group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper:items-center
//   group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper:flex-1
//   group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper:flex-row
//   group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper:items-start
//   group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper:gap-4
//   data-[disabled]:pointer-events-none data-[disabled]:opacity-50
```

#### `StepperTrigger` — Clickable step button
```tsx
// Props: React.ComponentProps<"button"> (no extra props)
// Reads useStepper() for onStepChange; reads useStepperItem() for step/state/disabled
// Renders: <button data-slot="stepper-trigger" data-state={state} onClick={()=>onStepChange(step)}>
//            <span data-state={state}>   ← indicator circle
//              {state==="completed" ? <CheckIcon size-4 /> : <span>{step}</span>}
//            </span>
//            {children}
//          </button>
// Button classes:
//   inline-flex flex-col items-center gap-2 outline-none text-sm font-medium
//   disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50
//   focus-visible:ring-[3px] focus-visible:ring-ring/50 focus-visible:outline-none rounded-sm
// Indicator <span> classes:
//   flex size-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border-2 transition-all
//   border-border bg-muted text-muted-foreground
//   data-[state=active]:border-primary data-[state=active]:bg-primary data-[state=active]:text-primary-foreground
//   data-[state=completed]:border-primary data-[state=completed]:bg-primary data-[state=completed]:text-primary-foreground
```

#### `StepperTitle` — Step label
```tsx
// Props: React.ComponentProps<"p">
// Reads useStepperItem() for state
// Renders: <p data-slot="stepper-title" data-state={state}>
// Classes:
//   text-sm font-medium leading-none text-muted-foreground
//   data-[state=active]:text-foreground data-[state=completed]:text-foreground
```

#### `StepperDescription` — Step sub-label
```tsx
// Props: React.ComponentProps<"p">
// Renders: <p data-slot="stepper-description">
// Classes: text-xs text-muted-foreground
// (No state-based styling — always muted, like CardDescription)
```

#### `StepperSeparator` — Connector line between steps
```tsx
// Props: afterStep (number) — which step this separator follows; React.ComponentProps<"div">
// Lives as a direct child of <Stepper> between <StepperItem> nodes (same as <BreadcrumbSeparator>)
// Reads useStepper() for orientation and activeStep
// isCompleted = afterStep < activeStep
// Renders: <div data-slot="stepper-separator" aria-hidden="true">
// Classes:
//   shrink-0 bg-border transition-colors
//   (isCompleted && "bg-primary")
//   group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper:h-px
//   group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper:flex-1
//   group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper:min-w-8
//   group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper:self-center
//   group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper:w-px
//   group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper:min-h-8
//   group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper:ml-4
//   group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper:self-stretch
// NOTE: ml-4 = 16px = center of 32px (size-8) circle for vertical alignment
```

#### `StepperContent` — Step body content panel
```tsx
// Props: React.ComponentProps<"div">
// Reads useStepperItem() for state; hidden unless state==="active"
// Renders: <div data-slot="stepper-content" data-state={state} hidden={state!=="active"}>
// Classes: hidden data-[state=active]:block
```

